Oshkosh.First Presbyterian Church (Oshkosh, Wisc:
First Presbyterian Church is a historic church at 110 Church Avenue in Oshkosh, Wisconsin, United States.
It was designed by Walter A. Holbrook of Milwaukee and built in 1893. The style is Richardsonian-Romanesque, with a complex, irregular profusion of turrets, chimneys and towers resembling Richardson's early libraries, meant to suggest it had been gradually added onto over many years.
